	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Quietust</b> [ Thu Jul 27, 2006 5:46 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Celius wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">The one I have is from rom hustler, and it came with 5 different ones. One has this computer screen with a bunch of colors flashing all over the place, and one has a kind of DOS startup looking thing. Which one's the actual thing? And there's a line that says "Kasetto no bakkappu suichi o OFF ni shite kudasai". Does that translate to "Please turn the backup switch OFF"? I'm not really sure what to do here, because I've never really dealt with this game, if you call it that.</div>
<br />
<br />I discovered that when it prints that message, it's actually complaining that it can't write to SRAM at $6000-$7FFF - evidently, it has a memory protection switch on it. Family Basic is one of the few "mapper 0" games that actually <strong>needs</strong> to have PRG RAM.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


